The paper deals with image processing and specifically with CT Metal Artifacts Reduction. The proposed method is based on convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of partial convolutions, which is a technique commonly used in image inpainting (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and formulation of the problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves numerical optimization, which is a common technique used in neural networks (cs.NE).
